			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This is done.  Enabling this in Chromium is tracked by issue 2651.

I ended up implementing this using the debug process rather than an NTDLL patch, which makes x86-32 and x86-64 more consistent.  The main reason was so that we can catch stack overflows.  Avoiding the red zone issue is a nice extra.

We might have to consider the NTDLL patch approach in the future for performance reasons, though.
